//--> to Contents , 本文へ May 11, 2017 Corporate PDF (98KB) For Immediate Release Company name: DAIICHI SANKYO COMPANY, LIMITED Representative: Sunao Manabe, Representative Director, President and COO (Code no.: 4568, First Section, Tokyo Stock Exchange) Please address inquiries to Noriaki Ishida, Executive Officer, Vice President, Corporate Communications Department Telephone: +81-3-6225-1126 http://www.daiichisankyo.com Differences Between Consolidated Results for Fiscal 2016 and Fiscal 2015 Tokyo, Japan (May 11, 2017) – Daiichi Sankyo Company, Limited (hereafter, Daiichi Sankyo) today announced that differences have arisen between its consolidated results for fiscal 2016 (from April 1, 2016 to March 31, 2017) and fiscal 2015 (from April 1, 2015 to March 31, 2016). 1. Differences between consolidated results for fiscal 2016 and fiscal 2015 Revenue Operating profit Profit before tax Profit for the year Profit attributable to owners of the Company Basic Earnings per share Millions of yen Millions of yen Millions of yen Millions of yen Millions of yen Yen Results of fiscal 2015 (A) 986,446 130,412 122,388 80,399 82,282 119.37 Results of fiscal 2016 (B) 955,124 88,929 87,788 47,479 53,466 79.63 Change (B-A) –31,321 –41,483 –34,600 –32,920 –28,816 – Percentage of change (%) –3.2 –31.8 –28.3 –40.9 –35.0 – 2. Reason for the differences Significant difference in profit for the year have arisen between the results of fiscal 2016 and the results of fiscal 2015 mainly due to the fact that an impairment loss related to the property, plant and equipment and intangible assets for the vaccine business was recorded in fiscal 2016 in addition to a decrease in revenue of Olmesartan. (Daiichi Sankyo discloses the difference in profit for the year when there is a significant difference between the actual result of profit for the year and that of the previous fiscal as it does not typically disclose the forecast of profit for the year.) The above figures for revenue, operating profit, profit before tax, profit for the year, profit attributable to owners of the Company, and basic earnings per share are the same as those disclosed in the Consolidated Financial Results for Fiscal 2016 which is also released today. Back to index
